Preheat oven to 325 degrees. Grease and flour a 12-cup bundt pan or 10-cup tube pan and sprinkle nuts over bottom of pan. In a large mixing bowl combine cake mix, pudding mix, eggs, BACARDI(R) Gold Rum, oil and water. Using an electric mixer beat at low speed until moistened. Beat at high speed 2 minutes. Pour batter over nuts. Bake 1 hour or until a skewer inserted in the cake comes out clean. Cool 15 minutes, then invert onto serving plate. Melt butter in saucepan. Stir in sugar, water and BACARDI(R) Gold Rum. Boil 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat. Prick top of cake with a fork. Spoon and brush glaze evenly over the top and sides. Allow cake to absorb glaze.